title: CityJS
description: CityJS Conference is a JavaScript festival across London, a joint event from the London's JavaScript meetups, including London JS Community, JS Monthly, Halfstack and Node User Group.

title: QCon
description: QCon London is a conference for senior software engineers and architects on the patterns, practices, and use cases leveraged by the world's most innovative software shops.

title: IndieWebCamp London [ONLINE ONLY]
description: IndieWebCamp London 2020 is a gathering for independent web creators of all kinds, from graphic artists, to designers, UX engineers, coders, hackers, to share ideas, actively work on creating for their own personal websites, and build upon each others creations.

title: LeadDev Live
description: We're talking about how to be the most effective engineering leader in these uncertain times. Join the Lead Dev community as we work this out together in 2 days of inspiring talks and interactive sessions.

title: LockdownConf
description: A Free Online Conference to Help You Prepare for a Post-Pandemic World

title: AllTheTalks.online
description: A collaborative effort of speakers, organizers and sponsors from around the world to provide a platform for the talks that have been cancelled due to the COVID-19 outbreak. Join us for 23.999 hours of talks, panels and activities while raising funds to assist select charities benefiting virus victims.

title: Python Pizza
description: Python Pizza is a micro conference organized by the Python Community. And this one is a truly special edition, a virus won't keep us apart!

title: SoCraTes UK 2020 Digital Spring
description: SoCraTes UK Digital Spring is a digital international Software Craft and Testing retreat for open-minded craftspeople who want to improve their craft and the software industry as a whole. This will be the first digital version of the well-known SoCraTes UK

title: Continuous Lifecycle London
description: Continuous Lifecycle London brings you together with the finest minds in DevOps, Containers, Continuous Delivery and Cloud Native development. Over three days of conference sessions and hands-on workshops, our speakers will take you through fundamental concepts, analyse real world scenarios, and explore key tools and technologies in depth, so that you can accelerate your own software development and deployment transformation.

title: Devoxx
description: Devoxx UK is a 3-day conference where developers and architects come together and explore the latest technology advancements and fascinating ideas, with some of the most inspiring speakers in our sector.

title: Software Design and Development
description: SDD 2020 features 112 in-depth sessions and workshops on a wide range of key software development topics, delivered by 43 world-class speakers.

title: Lead Dev London
description: Join our community at the Lead Dev London, where technical leaders learn to nurture high performing teams, apply the best tech and tools for the job, and thrive as they meet the challenges of software engineering leadership.

title: Devopsdays London
description: Devopsdays is a worldwide series of technical conferences covering topics of software development, IT infrastructure operations, and the intersection between them. Each event is run by volunteers from the local area.

title: Code Mesh London
description: We bring together a unique mix of creators, developers, innovators, academics, and visionaries to help solve real-world problems using innovative, non-mainstream tech.

title: ACCU Conference
description: Taking place across four days, ACCU is the conference for all those interested in native languages and professionalism in programming. As in previous years, two of the five streams will focus purely on C++.

title: C++ on Sea
description: The international C++ conference in the UK, by the sea
